  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through several key strategies:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Requirement for financial institutions to verify client identities\n\n2. Investigation Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Use of advanced digital tracking technologies\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- Coordinated investigations\n\n4. Prosecution Strategies\n- Targeting financial intermediaries\n- Seizing assets\n- Criminal charges for money laundering\n- Significant financial penalties\n\n5. Regulatory Compliance\n- Banks required to implement robust compliance programs\n- Regular audits and reporting\n- Strict penalties for non-compliance\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and financial frameworks.",
